# RULES: REDROB Custom Character Creator Web App

## GENERAL
- Build a web app that allows users to create custom character avatars.
- Reference visual/UX behavior from https://faces.notion.com/.
- Use React or Next.js unless otherwise specified.
- Use SVG or Canvas layers for rendering.

## MAIN PAGE REQUIREMENTS
- On load: generate a random characters preview.
- 3 rows of randomly created characters in a infinite carousel. Each row should have different speed settings and should have different start position.
- Provide a CTA: “시작하기 +”.

## CUSTOMIZE PAGE LAYOUT
- Left panel: customization controls with lists of categories: skin tone, eyes, nose, mouth, hair, accessories. Takes 5 columns out of 12 column grid system.
- Right: real-time preview (round shape in 540px size) that takes 7 columns out of 12 column grid system. Below a preview, two action buttons (56px): Surprise Me which is a button that randomize characters, and reset button in round icon button that resets everything.


## CUSTOMIZATION CONTROLS
All components must support:
- Color picker
- Size slider
- X/Y position adjustment
- Variant/style selection

Components:
- Face: color, contour style.
- Hair: style, color.
- Eyes: style, color, size, spacing slider, rotation slider.
- Nose: size, position.
- Mouth: style, size.
- Background: solid/gradient/pattern.

## PREVIEW REQUIREMENTS
- All changes must update preview instantly.
- Preview must support responsive layout.
- (Optional) zoom controls.

## ACTION BUTTONS
- Reset: resets current element.
- Randomize: randomizes all or selected attributes.
- Download PNG:
  - Export 1024×1024 PNG.
  - Option: include or exclude background.
  - Filename: REDROB_avatar_[timestamp].png.

## TECHNICAL NOTES
- Use layered rendering (SVG or Canvas).
- For PNG export: compose layers → `toDataURL()` → download.
- Maintain clean component structure: one component per attribute category.
- Ensure attributes are JSON-configurable for future algorithmic randomization.

## FUTURE-READY (OPTIONAL)
- User login + save/load presets.
- Animation support.
- Shareable links for generated avatars.


## TYPOGRAPHY SYSTEM

- Use "Pretendard" as the primary font family across the entire product.
- Do not introduce additional font families.
- Maintain consistent typographic hierarchy using predefined text styles only.

